  <text type="poesis">
      <body>
         <div met="hendecasyllabus">
            <head>Tranquillus Parthenius Andronicus Dalmata lectori verum describit philosophum.</head>



            <l>Hic est maximus ille quem requiris,</l>
            <l>Nulli par hominum, minus secundus,</l>
            <l>Nunquam sollicitus, dolore nullo.</l>
            <l>Quem nec vanus amor metusve rodit:</l>
            <l n="5">Ignarusque animi furoris: atqui</l>
            <l>Nec vitae cupidus, sibi nec ipsi</l>
            <l>Indulgens nimium: sed usque constans.</l>
            <l>Quem nec frigora, nec gelu, nec aestus,</l>
            <l>Imbres nec madidi, niuesque dirae,</l>
            <l n="10">Ventorum aut rabies trucisque saeua</l>
            <l>Non fati series mouere possunt:</l>
            <l>Quin semper putet esse se beatum,</l>
            <l>Fortunae dominus, suique rector.</l>
            <l>Hunc si partibus assequi licebit</l>
            <l n="15">Cunctis: Quis neget Herculem, Iouemque</l>
            <l>Caessuros animo tuo decenti?</l>
         </div>    
      </body>
